              "question": "Why are sociologists interested in studying the natural environment?\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
              "order": "randomized",
              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "Studying the environment helps us better understand political and social divisions."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "Human development and progress is modeled after changes that take place in the natural world."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "Environmental problems result from the choices and actions of human beings, which means they are social problems."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "Animals and plant communities interact socially in much the same way that humans do. Therefore, sociologists believe they can learn about humans by watching these natural interactions."
